org.eclipse.incquery.uml.derivedfeatures

Class ProtocolTransitionReferredMatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.impl.BasePatternMatch
      • org.eclipse.incquery.uml.derivedfeatures.ProtocolTransitionReferredMatch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, IPatternMatch

    public abstract class ProtocolTransitionReferredMatch
extends BasePatternMatch
    Pattern-specific match representation of the org.eclipse.incquery.uml.derivedfeatures.protocolTransitionReferred pattern, to be used in conjunction with ProtocolTransitionReferredMatcher.

    Class fields correspond to parameters of the pattern. Fields with value null are considered unassigned. Each instance is a (possibly partial) substitution of pattern parameters, usable to represent a match of the pattern in the result of a query, or to specify the bound (fixed) input parameters when issuing a query.

    See Also:
    ProtocolTransitionReferredMatcher, ProtocolTransitionReferredProcessor

      • newMatch

        public static ProtocolTransitionReferredMatch newMatch(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.ProtocolTransition pSelf,
                                                       org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Operation pOperation)
        Returns a new (partial) match. This can be used e.g. to call the matcher with a partial match.

        The returned match will be immutable. Use newEmptyMatch() to obtain a mutable match object.

        Parameters:
        pSelf - the fixed value of pattern parameter self, or null if not bound.
        pOperation - the fixed value of pattern parameter operation, or null if not bound.
        Returns:
        the (partial) match object.
